Majalisar Dinkin Duniya ta ce da akwai dubban mayaka masu kyamar Pakistan a Afghanistan
ISLAMABAD -- Wani rahoto na Majalisar Dinkin Duniya ya ce da akwai sama da 'yan tawayen Pakistan 6,000 da ke boye a Afghanistan, yawancinsu 'yan haramtacicyar kungiyar Taliban ne da ke da alhakkin kai hare-hare kan wuraren sojoji da kuma fararen hula a Pakistan.
Rahoton wanda aka fitar a wannan makon ya ce kungiyar wacce ake kira Tehreeek-e-Talibanm (TTP), na da alaka da kungiya masu fafutuka ta Islama da ke Afghan.
Wasu daga cikin mambobin TTP sun shiga kungiya mai alaka da IS, da ke da shalkwatarta a gabashin Afghanistan.
Gwamnatin Afghanistan ba ta amsa bukatar da kamfanin dillacin labarai na Associated Press ta aika don jin ta bakinsu.
Rahoton ya ce kungiyar IS a Afghanistan wacce a ke kira da IS ta gundumar Khorosan, Sojojin Afghan da na Amurka da kuma na kungiyar NATO, a wasu lokutan ma har da na Afghan Taliban su sha kai musu hare-hare.
Bangaren masu bin diddigia da sa ido na Majalisar Dinkin Duniya da ke bibiyar kungiyoyin'yan ta'adda a duniya ne suka shirya rahoton.
Rahoton ya kiyasta magoya bayan kungiyar IS a Afghanistan ya kai 2,200 yayin da aka dakusar da shugabancinta, kungiyar IS na kirga dan asalin Syria Abu Sa'id Mohammed Alkhorasani a cikin a shugabaninta.
